         <div type="translation">
            <ab>[.]fourth. ;In the ninth year of the Emperor Caesar Nerva Traianus Augustus Germanicus Dacicus, month Sebastos, 30, at Theadelphia of the Themistou meris of the Arsinoite nome. Athenarion [ ], aged about 32 years old with her guardian NN, a nephew from her father's family, aged about 33 years old, scar [ ] acknowledges to [Philippos, son of NN], aged about 33 years old, scar [ ] that neither Athenarion nor her assigns take action ] ...  nor in the future will take action against Philippos ... [The following text  is too fragmentary to translate]</ab>
         </div>
